Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1613):
The tab buttons set `aria-controls` to their panel IDs, but each tab panel is conditionally rendered with `v-if`. When a tab is not active, its referenced panel element doesn’t exist in the DOM, which makes the ARIA relationship invalid for assistive technologies. Prefer keeping all panels mounted (e.g., `v-show` + `hidden` on inactive panels) so `aria-controls` always points to an existing element.
Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, keep each top-level tabpanel section mounted so every tab button's aria-controls target exists in the DOM. Replace the four top-level panel v-if directives for notifications-configuration-panel, notifications-health-panel, notifications-deliveries-panel, and notifications-diagnostics-panel with v-show="activeTab === '<tab>'" and add :hidden="activeTab !== '<tab>'" to each same section. Preserve the existing id, role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby, classes, and all inner content. Do not change selectNotificationTab(), ensureActiveTabDataLoaded(), or any data-loading behavior; this is only a template accessibility fix for the panel elements controlled by the tab buttons.
